\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "proof:general publication bias"

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $n=1$
\end_inset

 and consider confidence sets for 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{0}$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\Pi$
\end_inset

 be the partitioning of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $p,q\in\pi$
\end_inset

 if and only if they share the same 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{0}$
\end_inset

, and let 
\begin_inset Formula $||[p]||=|\theta_{0}|$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $||f^{k}||=|\theta_{0}|$
\end_inset

 from the mixture representation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:mixture model formulation"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Using Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "lem:generalized shifted exponential"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we see that 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{k},k>1$
\end_inset

 converges pointwise to a truncated exponential when 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{0}=-n$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{\tau^{2}+\sigma^{2}}=n^{1/2}$
\end_inset

, so that (i), (ii), (iii) of Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:Mixture model corollary"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 are satisfied with 
\begin_inset Formula $K'=K\backslash\{1\}$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

s can be fixed at e.g.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi=1/(K-1)$
\end_inset

, and (iv) is satisfied as well.
 The proofs for 
\begin_inset Formula $||[p]||=\tau$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $||[p]||=\sqrt{\tau^{2}+\theta_{0}^{2}}$
\end_inset

 are similar and omitted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
When 
\begin_inset Formula $n>1$
\end_inset

, we are dealing with
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\prod_{j=1}^{n}\sum_{k\leq K}\pi_{i}^{k}(\sigma_{j})f_{i}^{k}(\sigma_{j}),\label{eq:product mixture}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and we cannot choose the same 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{\tau^{2}+\sigma_{i}^{2}}=n^{1/2}$
\end_inset

 for all of the mixture components simultaneously whenever some 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{i}$
\end_inset

s aren't equal, which is usually the case.
 But it is clear that Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand pageref
reference "lem:generalized shifted exponential"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 also works for 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau^{2}=n+c$
\end_inset

 for any constant 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

, so this does not matter matters.
 Now expand the expression in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:product mixture"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and do the same reasoning as in the first part of this proof.
\end_layout

